Restore Python 2 compatiblity

The port to python 3 broke two things:
- Printing the rendered result without b'' around it
- Checking whether something is a string under python2

To address this, the following was done:
- Always use the print_function, no matter what the python version.
  This is for consistent behavior.
- Factor out text check into its own function.
- Tell ElementTree's tostring function to use the right encoding
  depending on python version.

Fix remove_invisible not working

Prior to this, using {: or :} for brackets would not prune the invisible
elements from output. Since getchildren() is not a direct view on the
children of an element, deleting from ns[i].getchildren() has no effect.

In order to actually remove an XML element, the parent needs to be
directly passed. Then, the parent's remove method must be called since
that will look up the child by instance before deleting it.

Finally, make these test cases readable. It's hard to read the test
cases when they span so many columns.

Pass testBar

The code before was not backwards parsing for symmetrical parenthesis
like the comments said. This resulted in expressions being properly
bracketed whenever | or || was involved.

The fix for this comes in three parts:

- Properly test whether we are starting a nest.
  For symmetrical brackets, we must parse **backwards** to collect the
  appropriate contents into its own mrow.
  If not, then leave it alone.
- make find_node_backwards report the proper index since the previous
  result would always report the node ahead of the target.
- Properly test whether the descending expression actually finishes off
  our set of brackets.

The fix so far doesn't wrap the solo symmetrical brackets in their own <mrow>s.
Why? They're treated as infix expressions in those cases, so it makes no
sense for them to be treated as their own group.

Prior to this, all minuses were grouped with numbers unconditionally.

asciimathml spec v2.2 updates

To support the update spec, a few changes were made to the internal API:

- Addition of o1_attr and o2_attr optional parameters to binary function. This allows
  binary operators that take arguments to set attributes instead of
  adding children nodes. The unary function should probably allow
  similar parameters for future use cases too.
- strip_tags function to get plaintext render of a node's children
- Addition of rewrite_lr optional parameter for the unary function. This
  allows unary operators to apply specific bracket types to a term
  without actually surrounding it in those braces.
- Various symbol mappings that didn't exist in before spec v2.2
